<p>India’s government has presented its annual national budget for 2026-27, putting major emphasis on infrastructure building and boosting domestic manufacturing as global trade tensions and volatile markets add uncertainty for exporters and investors. The plan includes higher capital spending on projects such as transport links, alongside measures aimed at strengthening supply chains in areas seen as strategically important, including minerals and digital infrastructure. Officials also said the budget aims to support growth while keeping an eye on fiscal discipline, signaling an effort to balance development goals with stable public finances.</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/-fEyP0LYCwMOAXI4rLzJXNQWsXk7Wk2sK4anXuRK-2UWNL0E8A80xcJKQMWUvZZCOYXZPRDjmXnO-35hPth42MdVgtsb0073lteeQwkXOfEhS_Qf7dvWK3GmQmcHrOMYGa77HrXPHemme2TjNpXdUotuzv2TF82WFJamyzOmbA' alt='India’s budget announcement as the government outlines spending priorities for 2026-27.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Capital outlay rise: India increased infrastructure spending by 8.8% to a record 12.2 trillion rupees for 2026-27, according to reporting shared in the discussion of the announcement.</li><li>Defense emphasis: The budget boosts defense allocations, a move DW links to expectations after last May’s four-day conflict with Pakistan.</li><li>High-speed rail: India’s budget highlights plans for seven high-speed rail corridors as part of its infrastructure push.</li><li>Rare earth corridors: The government announced dedicated rare earth corridors across four mineral-rich states to strengthen domestic supply chains and reduce reliance on China for critical minerals used in clean energy, electronics and defense.</li><li>Data centre incentives: The budget includes tax breaks aimed at attracting investment in data centres as India tries to expand domestic capacity for fast-growing digital demand.</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Indian government: The budget is designed to sustain economic growth while maintaining fiscal discipline despite market volatility. (<a href='https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/indias-budget-boosts-infrastructure-spending-vowing-fiscal-discipline-129749015'>ABC News</a>)</li><li>Policy analysts covering the budget: The spending and incentives reflect a push to localise strategic supply chains—spanning rare earths, semiconductors, and cloud/data infrastructure—amid rising geopolitical and trade tensions. (<a href='https://www.firstpost.com/explainers/india-budget-2026-geopolitics-rare-earths-semiconductors-nuclear-defence-explained-13974921.html'>Firstpost</a>)</li><li>Economic observers cited in coverage: The budget’s tilt toward infrastructure and manufacturing is framed as a response to global trade uncertainty and volatile financial markets. (<a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/2/1/indias-budget-bets-on-infrastructure-manufacturing-amid-global-trade-war'>Al Jazeera</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/2/1/indias-budget-bets-on-infrastructure-manufacturing-amid-global-trade-war'>India’s budget bets on infrastructure, manufacturing amid global trade war</a> - aljazeera.com</li><li><a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/c3dm790vxlko'>Rare earths and data centres: India pushes local industry as global tensions rise</a> - bbc.com</li><li><a href='https://www.reddit.com/r/worldnews/comments/1qss24j/india_raises_infrastructure_spending_by_88_to/'>India raises infrastructure spending by 8.8% to record 12.2 trillion rupees for 2026-27</a> - reddit.com</li><li><a href='https://www.dw.com/en/india-sets-record-budget-for-infrastructure-defense/a-75753459'>India sets record budget for infrastructure, defense</a> - dw.com</li><li><a href='https://www.firstpost.com/explainers/india-budget-2026-geopolitics-rare-earths-semiconductors-nuclear-defence-explained-13974921.html'>Semiconductors, defence and more... How geopolitics shaped India’s Budget 2026</a> - firstpost.com</li><